# ============================================================================
# SECURITY: Sensitive Data - NEVER COMMIT THESE FILES
# ============================================================================
# The following patterns protect sensitive information from being committed.
# If you accidentally commit sensitive data, immediately:
# 1. Rotate/regenerate all exposed secrets
# 2. Remove the data from git history (git filter-branch or BFG Repo-Cleaner)
# 3. Force push (if already pushed to remote)
# ============================================================================

# AWS credentials and secrets
**/secrets/
**/secrets.json
**/credentials.json
**/aws-credentials*
**/*-secrets.*
**/*-credentials.*
**/config.local.*
**/config.local.txt
**/config.production.*

# API keys and tokens
**/*-token*
**/*-key*
**/api-keys.*
**/tokens.*
